                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d124">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/4074: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister Resident in Ethiopia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Engert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Addis Ababa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-04-10T10:00:00+02:35"
                            >April 10, 1936—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 12—12:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>208. My 201, April 8, 11 a.m.,<note n="11" xml:id="d124fn11">Not printed.</note>
                    and Department’s 136, April 10, 5 p.m.<note n="12" xml:id="d124fn12">
                        <hi rend="italic">Infra.</hi>
                    </note> I now learn confidentially that the Ethiopian Government has received a
                    definite intimation from Geneva that in view of the military situation it was
                    useless to insist on the letter and the spirit of the League Covenant in
                    negotiating with Italy. After a conversation with the Emperor by telegraph the
                    Council of Ministers decided this morning to reply rejecting the suggestion and
                    emphasizing determination to negotiate only through the League. I gather this
                    decision was taken because military situation is not yet considered
                    hopeless.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
